sub_title: Coach learning strategies MILS Russian and Dutch / Psychologist/ Beroepsoverstijgende assessor / Owner Two Worlds
summary:
People is what interest me. What moves them and what stands behind their behaviors. 
My experiences go to content-development of assessments and measurements, maintaining them, describing the results and making report pages, making trainings, managing translations of psychological instruments into different languages with as little as possible loss of validity and reliability. 

What I appreciate the most in life is the ‘real thing’. If you want to know what I mean, then ask me!!  
I am easy with communicating and collaborating with people, appreciate humor and self-reflection.

The way we absorb and remember information is different for everyone. We are not always aware that we have a preference in this. For example, one person prefers to read text and another prefers to listen, for some pictures may be important or regular exercise may be necessary. All are talents we have that are important for us to process information quickly and easily. If we don't know what our personal preferences are we will not act accordingly and working and learning will take much more time and energy than we really want.
MILS coach helps to find out what learning preferences a person has. Knowing that, we can together work out the best strategies to learn easier en more effective.
